column5: I was thinking of doing to Byng Island conservation area in the spring and fishing there if they're open before the the official May 1st caming opening. Does anyone know if they keep it locked up, open it up like some other places or just charge day fee for admission?
I went in there in march one year to fish cats, the gate has a chain across it but you can park on the road and walk in.
Thats what I have in mind  I guess I can do that.
I believe there is a dock, small launch area on the opposite side of the river that you could try.
